# CampuGrid ‚Äî Comprehensive Gap Analysis & Implementation Plan

After cross-referencing `chat.md`, `chat2.md`, all 7 phase plans from `artifacts/`, and the actual codebase, here is every missing piece.

---

## Executive Summary

The **server backend** (Phases 1‚Äì4) is ~90% complete. The **web frontend** (Phase 5) is ~70% complete. The **Tauri daemon** (Phase 6) is ~40% complete. Phase 7 (polish & landing) is ~30% complete. The critical missing pieces are all around the **Contributor Experience** ‚Äî there's no way for a contributor to authenticate, register nodes, view earnings, or see a leaderboard from *either* the web app or the Tauri app.

---

## Gap 1: Web App ‚Äî Missing Contributor Pages

The original Phase 5 plan and Phase 6 plan both reference a web-based contributor management flow. Currently the web app only has customer-facing pages.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> There is **no page in the web app** where a user can register a node and get a JWT token to paste into their Tauri app. This is the critical missing link.

### What needs to be built:

| Page | Route | Purpose |
|------|-------|---------|
| **Contributor Dashboard** | `/contributor` | Shows user's registered nodes, their status (online/offline), earnings summary, reliability scores |
| **Node Registration** | `/contributor/register` | Form to register a new node ‚ûú returns Node UUID + JWT auth token for the Tauri app |
| **Earnings & History** | `/contributor/earnings` | Billing records from the contributor perspective (uses existing `/billing/earnings` API) |
| **Leaderboard** | `/contributor/leaderboard` | Campus rankings (Phase 6 plan lines 303‚Äì335) |

### What already exists in the backend:
- ‚úÖ `POST /nodes/register` ‚Äî creates a node
- ‚úÖ `GET /nodes/me` ‚Äî lists user's nodes 
- ‚úÖ `GET /billing/earnings` ‚Äî contributor earnings
- ‚úÖ `GET /billing/history` ‚Äî billing records
- ‚ùå `GET /leaderboard` ‚Äî **not built**
- ‚ùå Node-specific JWT generation ‚Äî **not built** (Tauri needs a dedicated token)

---

## Gap 2: Tauri Daemon ‚Äî No Auth/Login Flow

> [!CAUTION]
> The Tauri app **has zero authentication**. It generates a random `node_id` on first launch and connects to the WebSocket with a hardcoded `internal_node` token. There is absolutely no login screen.

### What the Phase 6 plan specifies (lines 457‚Äì468):
1. First-run: auto-detect GPU, check Docker
2. **Registration flow: creates account ‚Üí registers node with server**
3. System tray icon states
4. Dashboard with real-time earnings

### What actually exists:
- ‚úÖ Hardware detection (`hw_detector.rs`)
- ‚úÖ Docker check (`docker_manager.rs`)  
- ‚úÖ WebSocket connection (`websocket.rs`)
- ‚úÖ Persistent node ID (`lib.rs` ‚Üí `node_id.txt`)
- ‚úÖ Dashboard UI, WorkloadView, SettingsView (React)
- ‚ùå **Login/Setup screen** ‚Äî completely missing
- ‚ùå **Token storage** ‚Äî no secure credential store
- ‚ùå **History page** ‚Äî planned in Phase 6 (line 271) but not built
- ‚ùå **Leaderboard page** ‚Äî planned in Phase 6 (line 303) but not built
- ‚ùå **Earnings panel** in Dashboard ‚Äî shows mock GPU gauge but no real earnings data
- ‚ùå **System tray** ‚Äî Tauri tray integration not wired

